1. LANGUAGE: Use deep, authentic Jamaican Patois (Patwa). Use correct tense markers: 'a' (pres cont), 'did' (past), 'a go' (future), 'haffi' (must).
2. GRAMMAR: Follow zero copula rules ("Di riddim sweet" instead of "The riddim is sweet"). Use focus marker 'a' for emphasis.
3. SOUL: Include soulful ad-libs (e.g., "(Woooah-oy!)", "(Jah Know!)") and elongated vowels for sustained notes.
4. STRUCTURE: Respect the user-defined song structure exactly. Use [Section Name] labels.
5. DJ TOAST: If a DJ Toast is requested, deliver high-energy, percussive rhythmic speech tailored to the selected persona.
6. TITLE: Provide a unique title in double quotes on the first line.

VOCABULARY & IDIOMS:
- Rastafarian Terms (The "I" Language):
  * "I-n-I": We/Us/I (signifying unity with the divine).
  * "Ital": Natural, saltless, pure (usually referring to food or lifestyle).
  * "Babylon": The oppressive system/government.
  * "Zion": The holy land/Africa/freedom.
  * "Reasoning": A deep, spiritual conversation.
  * "Medz": To meditate or think deeply.
  * "Hail up": To greet with respect.
- Street Slang & Common Talk:
  * "Gwan": Go on/What's happening.
  * "Link up": To meet up.
  * "Pickney": A child.
  * "Likkle more": See you later/Goodbye.
  * "Dawg/Bredda": Close friend or brother.
  * "Shell": To do something excellently (e.g., "shell di dance").
  * "Big up": To give praise or recognition.
- Common Idioms:
  * "Tun up di ting": Increase the intensity/level up.
  * "Step up inna di dance": Arriving at the party/scene.
  * "Nuff respect": Total respect.
  * "Red eye": To be envious or greedy.
  * "Hard ears": Stubborn.
  * "Salt": To be unlucky or jinxed.

PROVERBIAL WISDOM:
Naturally integrate these to add "Roots" weight:
  * "Wah eye nuh see, heart nuh leap" (Hidden struggles).
  * "Chicken merry, hawk deh near" (Danger lurks behind success).
  * "Every mickle mek a muckle" (Persistence leads to results).
  * "Rain a fall but dutty tough" (Times are hard despite relief).
  * "One one coco full basket" (Progress is gradual).
  * "Mi throw mi corn, but mi nuh call nuh fowl" (Indirect truth-telling).
  * "Trouble nuh set like rain" (No warning for misfortune).
  * "Empty barrel mek di most noise" (Ignorance is loud).
  * "If yuh waan good, yuh nose haffi run" (Success requires sacrifice).
  * "Better fi shadow leh yuh dan rain wet yuh" (Caution is key).
  * "Nuh bruck yuh bridge before yuh cross it" (Don't burn bridges).
  * "Cowad man keep soun' bone" (Avoid unnecessary conflict).
  * "Wah sweet a mout' hot a battam" (Pleasure can have consequences).
`;

export const generateLyrics = async (
  theme: string, 
  rhymeScheme: string, 
  djPersona: string, 
  songStructure: string[]
): Promise<GeneratedSong> => {

  const prompt = `
THEME: ${theme}
RHYME SCHEME: ${rhymeScheme}
DJ PERSONA: ${djPersona}
STRUCTURE: ${songStructure.join(' -> ')}

Task: Write a full Reggae song. Ensure the title is on the first line in quotes. 

STORYTELLING & LINGUISTIC REQUIREMENT: 
1. Naturally weave one or two of the Jamaican proverbs from your instructions into the lyrics.
2. Leverage the specialized VOCABULARY (Rastafarian terms, Street Slang, and Idioms) to ensure the Patois is deep and culturally accurate.
3. The flow must be rhythmic, fitting for a Reggae riddim. ad-libs should support the emotional weight of the theme.
`;

  for (let i = 0; i < MAX_RETRIES; i++) {
    try {
      const response = await ai.models.generateContent({
        model: "gemini-3-pro-preview",
        contents: prompt,
        config: {
          systemInstruction: SYSTEM_INSTRUCTION,
          temperature: 0.85,
          topP: 0.95,
        },
      });

      const text = response.text || "";
      const lines = text.trim().split('\n');
      const titleMatch = lines[0].match(/"(.*?)"/);
      const title = titleMatch ? titleMatch[1] : "Untitled Riddim";
      const lyrics = titleMatch ? lines.slice(1).join('\n').trim() : text;

      return { title, lyrics };
    } catch (err: any) {
      if (i === MAX_RETRIES - 1) throw err;
      await delay(BACKOFF_MS * Math.pow(2, i));
    }
  }
  throw new Error("Generation failed.");
};

import React, { useState, useCallback, useEffect, useRef } from 'react';
import { generateLyrics } from './services/geminiService';
import { logAction } from './services/auditLogService';
import { secureGetItem, secureSetItem, removeItem } from './services/storageService';
import Spinner from './components/Spinner';
import LyricsOutput from './components/LyricsOutput';
import History from './components/History';
import StructureBuilder from './components/StructureBuilder';
import HeaderIcon from './components/HeaderIcon';
import ThemeSwitcher from './components/ThemeSwitcher';
import AdminPanel from './components/AdminPanel';
import TestPanel from './components/TestPanel';

// Types
export interface HistoryEntry {
  id: number;
  theme: string;
  songTitle: string;
  artistName: string;
  albumName: string;
  lyrics: string;
  timestamp: string;
  rhymeScheme: string;
  djPersona: string;
  songStructure: string[];
}

export interface User {
  password: string;
  role: 'user' | 'admin';
  privacyAccepted?: boolean;
}

export type Theme = 'dark' | 'light' | 'high-contrast';
type View = 'main' | 'admin' | 'testing';

interface SpeechRecognition extends EventTarget {
  continuous: boolean;
  interimResults: boolean;
  lang: string;
  onstart: () => void;
  onend: () => void;
  onerror: (e: any) => void;
  onresult: (e: any) => void;
  start(): void;
  stop(): void;
}
declare global {
  interface Window {
    SpeechRecognition: any;
    webkitSpeechRecognition: any;
  }
}

const App: React.FC = () => {
  // --- Auth & Session (SOC 2 Governance) ---
  const [currentUser, setCurrentUser] = useState<string | null>(() => localStorage.getItem('patoisLyricistCurrentUser'));
  const [currentUserRole, setCurrentUserRole] = useState<'user' | 'admin'>('user');
  const [authView, setAuthView] = useState<'login' | 'register'>('login');
  const [authUsername, setAuthUsername] = useState('');
  const [authPassword, setAuthPassword] = useState('');
  const [privacyAccepted, setPrivacyAccepted] = useState(false);
  const [authError, setAuthError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [failedAttempts, setFailedAttempts] = useState(0);
  const [lockoutUntil, setLockoutUntil] = useState<number | null>(null);
  const [sessionTimeoutReached, setSessionTimeoutReached] = useState(false);
  const [showErasureConfirm, setShowErasureConfirm] = useState(false);

  // --- Laboratory State ---
  const [themeInput, setThemeInput] = useState<string>('');
  const [rhymeScheme, setRhymeScheme] = useState<string>('AABB');
  const [djPersona, setDjPersona] = useState<string>('Hype Man');
  const [songStructure, setSongStructure] = useState<string[]>(['Intro', 'Verse', 'Chorus', 'Verse', 'Chorus', 'DJ Toast', 'Outro']);
  const [lyrics, setLyrics] = useState<string>('');
  const [songTitle, setSongTitle] = useState<string>('');
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState<boolean>(false);
  const [currentView, setCurrentView] = useState<View>('main');
  const [history, setHistory] = useState<HistoryEntry[]>([]);

  // --- Voice & Session Timing ---
  const [isListening, setIsListening] = useState(false);
  const [isSpeechSupported, setIsSpeechSupported] = useState(false);
  const recognitionRef = useRef<SpeechRecognition | null>(null);
  const timeoutRef = useRef<number | null>(null);

  const THEME_LIMIT = 3000;
  const MAX_FAILED_ATTEMPTS = 3;
  const LOCKOUT_DURATION = 60 * 1000;
  const INACTIVITY_LIMIT = 15 * 60 * 1000;

  // --- SOC 2 Guardrails ---
  const resetInactivityTimer = useCallback(() => {
    if (timeoutRef.current) window.clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current);
    if (currentUser) {
      timeoutRef.current = window.setTimeout(() => {
        setSessionTimeoutReached(true);
        handleLogout();
      }, INACTIVITY_LIMIT);
    }
  }, [currentUser]);

  useEffect(() => {
    const events = ['mousedown', 'keydown', 'scroll', 'touchstart'];
    events.forEach(e => window.addEventListener(e, resetInactivityTimer));
    resetInactivityTimer();
    return () => {
      events.forEach(e => window.removeEventListener(e, resetInactivityTimer));
      if (timeoutRef.current) window.clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current);
    };
  }, [resetInactivityTimer]);

  useEffect(() => {
    const loggedInUser = localStorage.getItem('patoisLyricistCurrentUser');
    if (loggedInUser) {
      const users = secureGetItem<Record<string, User>>('patoisLyricistUsers') || {};
      if (users[loggedInUser]) {
        setCurrentUser(loggedInUser);
        setCurrentUserRole(users[loggedInUser].role);
        setHistory(secureGetItem<HistoryEntry[]>(`patoisLyricistHistory_${loggedInUser}`) || []);
      } else { handleLogout(); }
    }
    const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('patoisLyricistTheme') as Theme || 'dark';
    document.body.setAttribute('data-theme', savedTheme);
    if (window.SpeechRecognition || window.webkitSpeechRecognition) setIsSpeechSupported(true);
  }, []);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (currentUser) secureSetItem(`patoisLyricistHistory_${currentUser}`, history);
  }, [history, currentUser]);

  // --- Handlers ---
  const handleLogin = () => {
    if (lockoutUntil && Date.now() < lockoutUntil) {
      setAuthError(`Security Lockout active. Retry shortly.`);
      return;
    }
    const users = secureGetItem<Record<string, User>>('patoisLyricistUsers') || {};
    const user = users[authUsername];
    if (user && user.password === authPassword) {
      localStorage.setItem('patoisLyricistCurrentUser', authUsername);
      setCurrentUser(authUsername);
      setCurrentUserRole(user.role);
      setAuthUsername(''); setAuthPassword(''); setAuthError(null); setFailedAttempts(0);
      setHistory(secureGetItem<HistoryEntry[]>(`patoisLyricistHistory_${authUsername}`) || []);
      logAction(authUsername, 'Identity Verification Success', { forensics: true });
    } else {
      const attempts = failedAttempts + 1;
      setFailedAttempts(attempts);
      if (attempts >= MAX_FAILED_ATTEMPTS) setLockoutUntil(Date.now() + LOCKOUT_DURATION);
      setAuthError(`Verification Failed. ${MAX_FAILED_ATTEMPTS - attempts} attempts remaining.`);
      logAction(authUsername || 'unknown', 'Identity Verification Failure', { attempt: attempts });
    }
  };

  const handleRegister = () => {
    if (!authUsername.trim() || authPassword.length < 8) {
      setAuthError('Identity requires username & 8+ char password.'); return;
    }
    if (!privacyAccepted) { setAuthError('Privacy Consent Required.'); return; }
    const users = secureGetItem<Record<string, User>>('patoisLyricistUsers') || {};
    if (users[authUsername]) { setAuthError('Identity already exists.'); return; }
    users[authUsername] = { password: authPassword, role: authUsername === 'admin' ? 'admin' : 'user', privacyAccepted: true };
    secureSetItem('patoisLyricistUsers', users);
    logAction('system', 'Identity Enrollment', { username: authUsername });
    handleLogin();
  };

  const handleLogout = () => {
    logAction(currentUser || 'unknown', 'Session Termination', {});
    localStorage.removeItem('patoisLyricistCurrentUser');
    setCurrentUser(null); setHistory([]); setCurrentView('main');
  };

  const handleGenerate = useCallback(async () => {
    if (!themeInput.trim()) return;
    setIsLoading(true); setLyrics(''); setSongTitle('');
    try {
      const result = await generateLyrics(themeInput, rhymeScheme, djPersona, songStructure);
      setLyrics(result.lyrics);
      setSongTitle(result.title);
      setHistory(prev => [{
        id: Date.now(), theme: themeInput, songTitle: result.title, artistName: '', albumName: '', lyrics: result.lyrics,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(), rhymeScheme, djPersona, songStructure
      }, ...prev].slice(0, 50));
    } catch (err: any) {
      console.error(err);
    } finally { setIsLoading(false); }
  }, [themeInput, rhymeScheme, djPersona, songStructure]);

  const handleExport = (format: 'txt' | 'md') => {
    if (!lyrics) return;

    const content = `TITLE: ${songTitle || 'Untitled Riddim'}
THEME: ${themeInput}
RHYME SCHEME: ${rhymeScheme}
PERSONA: ${djPersona}
STRUCTURE: ${songStructure.join(' -> ')}

--------------------------------------------------

${lyrics}
`;

    const blob = new Blob([content], { type: 'text/plain' });
    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    const link = document.createElement('a');
    link.href = url;
    link.download = `${(songTitle || 'riddim').replace(/\s+/g, '_').toLowerCase()}.${format}`;
    document.body.appendChild(link);
    link.click();
    document.body.removeChild(link);
    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);

    logAction(currentUser || 'unknown', 'Export Lyrics', { format, title: songTitle });
  };

  if (!currentUser) {
    return (
      <div className="login-background" role="main">
        {sessionTimeoutReached && (
          <div className="fixed top-5 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 bg-yellow-600 text-black px-6 py-2 rounded-full font-bold z-50 shadow-2xl" role="alert">
            ⚠️ Security: Session Expired
          </div>
        )}
        <div className="login-container">
          <div className="login-header">
            <h1 className="login-logo">PATOISLyricist</h1>
            <p className="login-subtitle">SECURE RIDDIM LABORATORY</p>
          </div>
          <div className="login-card">
            <h2 className="card-title" id="auth-heading">{authView === 'login' ? 'Verification' : 'Enrollment'}</h2>
            {authError && <p className="text-red-400 text-center mb-4 text-sm font-bold bg-red-900/20 p-2 rounded" role="alert">{authError}</p>}
            <form onSubmit={e => { e.preventDefault(); authView === 'login' ? handleLogin() : handleRegister(); }} aria-labelledby="auth-heading">
              <div className="form-group">
                <label className="sr-only" htmlFor="username">Username</label>
                <input id="username" type="text" placeholder="Identity Handle" required value={authUsername} onChange={e => setAuthUsername(e.target.value)} />
              </div>
              <div className="form-group">
                <label className="sr-only" htmlFor="password">Password</label>
                <input id="password" type="password" placeholder="Access Token" required value={authPassword} onChange={e => setAuthPassword(e.target.value)} />
              </div>
              {authView === 'register' && (
                <div className="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <input id="consent" type="checkbox" checked={privacyAccepted} onChange={e => setPrivacyAccepted(e.target.checked)} className="accent-[#D4AF37] w-5 h-5" />
                  <label htmlFor="consent" className="text-xs opacity-60 cursor-pointer">I consent to SOC 2 local obfuscated processing.</label>
                </div>
              )}
              <button type="submit" className="login-btn">{authView === 'login' ? 'Validate Identity' : 'Enroll Identity'}</button>
              <p className="register-link">
                {authView === 'login' ? "New entity?" : "Existing entity?"} 
                <button type="button" onClick={() => setAuthView(authView === 'login' ? 'register' : 'login')} className="ml-2 underline text-title">{authView === 'login' ? 'Enroll' : 'Verify'}</button>
              </p>
            </form>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen relative" role="application">
      <div className="rasta-stripes" />
      <div className="container mx-auto p-6 max-w-4xl">
        <header className="mb-12 flex flex-col items-center">
          <div className="w-full flex justify-between items-center mb-6">
            <ThemeSwitcher onThemeChange={t => { document.body.setAttribute('data-theme', t); localStorage.setItem('patoisLyricistTheme', t); }} />
            <div className="text-right">
              <span className="text-xs opacity-50 block uppercase tracking-tighter">Current Identity: {currentUser}</span>
              <button onClick={handleLogout} className="text-xs font-black text-title hover:underline uppercase">Terminate Session</button>
